The paper deals with optimization problems in machine learning, specifically the problem of minimizing composite objective functions under R\'enyi differential privacy. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and numerical optimization (cs.NA). Additionally, the experiments involve real and simulated datasets, which could fall under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
